<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3430] Go THttpClient does not read HTTP response body to completion when closing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3430</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In THttpClient.closeResponse the body of the HTTP response is closed but the body itself is never explicitly read to completion. The go docs specify that if the response body is not read to completion and keepalive is enabled, the connection will never be returned to the pool.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
